;;
;; Fastener detail (added alongside the original 10 subassembly-level
;; lines, which are UNCHANGED above/below): the individual bolts/nuts/
;; washers/screws each subassembly's own fastening uses to attach to
;; the frame or to each other. Same "hand-authored, illustrative BOM"
;; disclaimer applies -- generic, common-sense fastener types/
;; quantities (M-series hex bolt + washer + nut "sets" and enclosure
;; screw/clamp "sets"), not a real fastener specification or vendor
;; part list. Each fastener line is consumed at exactly the station
;; that actually does that fastening (see compressor-unit-prod-
;; order.edn's `:station/parts`), never a bare loose orphan line.
;;
;; Additive-manufacturing swap (ADR-2800000400): the original
;; `part:fan-assembly` line ("Condenser fan assembly", a generic
;; bolted-sheet-metal-housing + separate-blade subassembly) is
;; replaced 1-for-1 below by `part:am-fan-housing`, an integrated
;; (single-piece) metal-3D-printed fan housing/impeller -- the kind of
;; complex, thin-walled, curved-blade geometry additive manufacturing
;; is well suited to and traditional sheet-metal fabrication is not.
;; Net BOM line count is UNCHANGED (still 16: the same 10 original +
;; 6 fastener lines, just this one line's content swapped) -- see
;; compressor-unit-prod-order.edn's new `st:am-print` station comment
;; for the equipment-asset link to cloud-itonami-isic-2822's
;; `:unit/metal-additive-manufacturing-system`.
{:bom/of :unit/industrial-refrigeration-compressor
 :bom/parts
 [{:part/id "part:compressor-body" :part/name "Compressor body (screw/reciprocating block)" :part/qty 1}
